metadata.name: Immortal Wings
metadata.description:
Immortal winged scarab, Khepri, were supposed to guarantee the reincarnation of the deceased, and were particularly popular burial amulets charmed with the Ankh (key of life) symbol of regeneration, were regarded to represent the force that drove the sun across the sky, and beyond the horizon each day.

Note: If you live in a state where recreational cannabis is legal, you can perfectly imitate the artist's mental state while creating this masterpiece.

1/1 Hand drawn, papyrus canvas, mixed media, illustration
Dimensions: 3013 × 3750px

Niko Todo
NFTYDELIC ART®
